title: Tyrodale
author: Marcus_Flaminius
pages:
#- 
§l      Suspense
          in
      Tyrodale
§r





§o            by
§r
        HapyBirdy
#- 
  CHAPTER 1:   My name is Eyriin, I currently am living in Tyrodale, the town with recent... Well.. no other way to say it, murder activites.  I decided that I should tell my cousin Iradessa, even if she won't believe me!  Time and Time again I think how
#- smart these murderers have been.  It's truly scary , still, I head out with my dear friend Magnolia who says her brother went after them. As we pass through the dead tree filled forest I can't stop the feeling I am being watched suddenly, out of the 
#- nearest dead branch, a crow flies followed by many more.  I had jumped at the sound of the screeching.  I stepped on a fallen branch and it snapped beneath my leather traveling boots.
  CHAPTER 2:   Blood. We have gone by a cave which had blood leading
#- into it. I couldn't tell if it was a bear den or not, Iradessa said we must go in... As we go into the cave a thunder storm begins to start. It echoes through the cave. Magnolia, Iradessa, and I fall down a steep rock slide in the cave. Magnolia is hurt,
#- her leg is broken and bleeding, Iradessa is unconscience. Magnolia tells me to go on alone.  I fear that if I leave them they might die, or I might.
  CHAPTER 3:  As I go deeper into the cave they fade from my view, and it gets colder. I hear 
#- someone talking, and I smell the scent of burnt flesh, which makes me grimace. I slowly crept near the noise slowly drawing my bow. I recognize who is making the noise it is Magnolia's brother, he has been hurt and was groaning. I wal kto him and ask why
#- hadn't he come back to Tyrodale. His answer is weak and he tells me that the murderers had been cooped up here. He then asks if anyone came with me, and I say in return, 'My cousin and your sister.'
  CHAPTER 4:  He has a terrified look on his face. He
#- says 'did you leave them alone!?' In response I say 'of 'course I did, the fell and were hurt, they asked me to go on. was there anything I should've worried about?' He stares at me blankly as if he were petrified, then he begins to cry. I ask him why he
#- is crying, and he says that they could've murdered them. I say that I could go back and tell them to come with me, he asks how do I know where to go. I ask him 'isn't the cave narrow?' he responds 'no' I grimace.
#- 
